<title>UK: EMI up again on merger speculation.</title>
<headline>EMI up again on merger speculation.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in EMI Plc were up 31p at 14.10 stg in light volume of 247,182 shares by 1000 GMT, on continued speculation that the company may be a likely candidate for a merger or takeover bid, market makers said.</p>
<p>&quot;The whole market is firmer and on days like this, the bid talk usually rears it head,&quot; one market maker said.</p>
<p>&quot;There is nothing new about this. EMI has been tipped as a bid target for sometime now.&quot;</p>
<p>Last month speculation intensified that Seagram's MCA music unit was interested in a link-up but EMI has denied it was in talks with MCA.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
